humanities required events at stanford humanities required facebook twitter email print add to calendar in this talk rosemary feal starts with the question are the humanities required by presenting the results of a recent mla project on college language requirements she then reviews trends in humanities study in higher education reflects on federal and state support for language and literary studies and analyzes the cultural moment in which higher education is situated today more than ever the united states needs educated people proficient in the humanities but the path to acquire advanced competence in language and literary studies has significant obstacles in it feal will describe those obstacles and point to some new directions the humanities education focal group explores issues concerning teaching and learning in the humanities including research on student learning innovation in pedagogy the role of new technologies in humanities instruction and professional issues for humanities teachers at all educational levels when wednesday march 7 2012 12 00 pm where pigott hall bldg 260 room 252 map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags arts lecture reading international humanities sponsor humanities education dlcl research unit focal group contact 650.724 1333 dlcl stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 313 31333 more info last modified march 6 2012
